  "prompt": "How do petrol pumps earn?",
  "response": "Petrol pumps (gas stations) earn revenue through multiple streams:\n\n1. Fuel Sales\n- Primary income from selling petrol, diesel, and other fuels\n- Profit margins are typically low, around 1-2% per liter\n- Volume of sales is crucial for profitability\n\n2. Convenience Store Sales\n- Selling snacks, beverages, cigarettes, and other quick-purchase items\n- Higher profit margins compared to fuel sales\n- Attracts customers and generates additional revenue\n\n3. Additional Services\n- Car wash facilities\n- Tire inflation and air services\n- Vehicle maintenance and repair services\n- Oil and lubricant sales\n\n4. Commission from Credit Card/Digital Payments\n- Small percentage earned from transaction processing\n\n5. Advertising and Rental Space\n- Renting space to advertisers\n- Leasing space to other businesses like small cafes or shops\n\n6. Ancillary Services\n- Auto repair shops\n- Quick service restaurants\n- ATM rentals\n\n7. Franchise or Brand Agreements\n- Some petrol pumps earn through brand partnerships and commissions\n\nThe profitability depends on location, fuel volume, additional services, and operational efficiency. Most earnings come from a combination of these revenue streams.",
